<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF87FF94FF7EFA97FBE0F924" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF87FF94FF7EFA97FE27F9D4" blockId="6.[136,1452,1346,2093]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FF7EFA97FEEBFABC" bold="true" box="[136,284,1346,1372]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves unknown, expanded submerged or floating leaves unknown; leaves of terrestrial plants obovate, 1.6–7.0 mm long × 0.7–5.0 mm wide, 3-nerved, sometimes with free veins from the midrib, as well as free and looped veins from the outer nerves. 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF87FF94FB26FA5EFB1EFA45" box="[1232,1257,1419,1445]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF87FF94FB1FFA5EFB0DFA45" box="[1257,1274,1419,1445]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
flowers usually in the same axil. Bracts linear, hyaline, caducous, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FD59FA7BFCC2FA29" box="[687,821,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
long. Styles persistent, erect, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FB88FA7BFAF3FA29" box="[1150,1284,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
long. Filament erect, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FF39FA07FEAFFA0D" box="[207,344,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2.5 mm</quantity>
long; anthers 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FE09FA07FD7FFA0D" box="[511,648,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FD10FA07FC98FA0D" box="[742,879,1490,1517]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
wide, possibly trilocular; pollen yellow. Fruit not strumose, subsessile, wider than high, light brown to blackish when mature, 0.6–1.0 mm long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF87FF94FB2AFA23FA92F9F1" box="[1244,1381,1526,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.3 mm</quantity>
wide, narrowly winged throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF87FF94FF4BF9EBFC26F9B8" blockId="6.[136,1452,1346,2093]" box="[189,977,1598,1625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FF4BF9EBFEAEF9B8" bold="true" box="[189,345,1598,1624]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF87FF94FE80F9EBFE29F9B9" box="[374,478,1598,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1655,1677]" captionTargetBox="[281,1310,984,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[273,1314,974,1631]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. The distribution of specimens of C. brutia in Oceania and Australasia based on records held by AVH." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577546/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Figures 4</figureCitation>
(a–b) and 4A(a–b) in 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FD27F9EAFC86F9B9" author="Mason, R." box="[721,881,1598,1625]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" pagination="295 - 327" refId="ref33979" refString="Mason, R. (1959) Callitriche in New Zealand and Australia. Australian Journal of Botany 7: 295 - 327. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / BT 9590295" type="journal article" year="1959">Mason (1959)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF87FF94FC8AF9EBFC3AF9B8" box="[892,973,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,225,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-31@4.[151,1436,190,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. antarctica, b—C. aucklandica, c—C. brachycarpa, d—C. brutia, e—C. capricorni, f—C. chathamensis, g—C. cyclocarpa i face on and ii end on, h—C. cycloptera, i—C. deflexa, j—C. fuliginea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577540/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF87FF94FF4BF9B7FBE0F924" blockId="6.[136,1452,1346,2093]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FF4BF9B7FEA1F99C" bold="true" box="[189,342,1634,1660]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FE84F9B6FDDEF99C" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1868" box="[370,553,1634,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FE84F9B6FDDEF99C" box="[370,553,1634,1661]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">C. brachycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FC3CF9B7FB54F99C" box="[970,1187,1634,1660]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FC3CF9B7FBB4F99C" box="[970,1091,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region by the combination of the small, unwinged, sessile fruit which is blackish when ripe, and ± isodiametric or wider than high and not umbonate, together with most leaf axils containing both 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF87FF94FCADF97FFC9DF924" box="[859,874,1706,1732]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF87FF94FC69F97EFC43F925" box="[927,948,1707,1733]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF87FF95FF4BF91BFBECF816" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="250" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF87FF94FF4BF91BFC94F898" blockId="6.[136,1452,1346,2093]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FF4BF91BFEAEF908" bold="true" box="[189,345,1742,1768]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Native. 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FE38F91BFD2AF908" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1868" box="[462,733,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FE38F91BFD2AF908" box="[462,733,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Callitriche brachycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF87FF94FC76F91BFC1DF908" box="[896,1002,1742,1768]" name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Australia</collectingCountry>
, where it occurs throughout the western lowlands and on King Island in 
<collectingRegion id="1D1EA194FF87FF94FE10F927FDA6F8EC" box="[486,593,1778,1804]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF87FF94FDA9F927FD55F8EC" box="[607,674,1778,1804]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[136,229,926,948]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[313,1273,190,902]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. The distribution of confirmed specimens of C. brachycarpa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580483/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). It is also known from six locations across 
<collectingRegion id="1D1EA194FF87FF94FB72F927FAE8F8EC" box="[1156,1311,1778,1804]" country="Australia" name="Victoria" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Victoria State</collectingRegion>
; three on the Otway Coast and three in the Port Phillip area (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FD6FF8C3FC54F8D1" author="Curtis, W. M. &amp; Morris, D. I." box="[665,931,1814,1841]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref30746" refString="Curtis, W. M. &amp; Morris, D. I. (1975) The student's flora of Tasmania. Part 1 Gymnosperms, Angiosperms: Ranunculaceae to Myrtacea e. 2 nd Ed. T. H. Hughes, Tasmania, Australia. 234 pp." type="book" year="1975">Curtis and Morris 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FC58F8C3FB78F8D0" author="Parks Victoria" box="[942,1167,1814,1840]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref34742" refString="Parks Victoria (2000) Yarra Bend Park: Environmental Action Plan. Parks Victoria, Deepdene, Victoria, Australia. 100 pp." type="book" year="2000">
Parks 
<collectingRegion id="1D1EA194FF87FF94FC05F8C3FBBAF8D0" box="[1011,1101,1814,1840]" country="Australia" name="Victoria" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Victoria</collectingRegion>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FB6EF8C3FAE9F8D0" author="Aston, H. I." box="[1176,1310,1814,1840]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref29662" refString="Aston, H. I. (1973) Aquatic plants of Australia. Melbourne University Press, Melbourne, Australia. 368 pp." type="book" year="1973">Aston 1973</bibRefCitation>
). It formerly occurred at a site subject to inundation on the northern outskirts of Melbourne (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FBFAF8EFFB6DF8B4" author="Jeanes, J. A." box="[1036,1178,1850,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref32394" refString="Jeanes, J. A. (1999) Callitrichaceae. In Walsh, N. G. &amp; Entwisle, T. J. (Eds.) Flora of Victoria. Vol 1. Dicotyledons, Cornaceae to Asteraceae. Inkata Press, Melbourne, Australia." type="book" year="1999">Jeanes 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FB50F8EEFAD5F8B4" author="Bean, A. R." box="[1190,1314,1850,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" pagination="545 - 554" refId="ref29812" refString="Bean, A. R. (2007) A taxonomic revision of Callitriche L. (Callitrichaceae) in Australia. Austrobaileya 7: 545 - 554." type="journal article" year="2007">Bean 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FADBF8EFFE8DF898" author="Threatened Species Section" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref36706" refString="Threatened Species Section (2012). King Island Biodiversity Management Plan. Department of Primary Industries, Parks, Water and Environment, Hobart, Australia. 144 pp." type="book" year="2012">Threatened Species Section 2012</bibRefCitation>
) but has apparently been lost from this site.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF87FF94FF4BF857FC81F7CD" blockId="6.[136,1452,1346,2093]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FF4BF857FE3EF87C" bold="true" box="[189,457,1922,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FE13F857FD01F87C" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1868" box="[485,758,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FE13F857FD01F87C" box="[485,758,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Callitriche brachycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in creeks and rivers or in damp hollows (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FAD6F857FA68F87C" author="Bean, A. R." box="[1312,1439,1922,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" pagination="545 - 554" refId="ref29812" refString="Bean, A. R. (2007) A taxonomic revision of Callitriche L. (Callitrichaceae) in Australia. Austrobaileya 7: 545 - 554." type="journal article" year="2007">Bean 2007</bibRefCitation>
), often in or near wet forest, but also in moist areas of dry sclerophyll forest and riparian scrub. It has been recorded with a range of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FEC9F81FFD7BF804" authority="L'Her. (1788: 18)" authorityName="L'Her." authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="1788" box="[319,652,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FEC9F81FFE4CF804" box="[319,443,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Eucalyptus</emphasis>
L’Hér. (1788: 18)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FD33F81FFC8EF804" box="[709,889,1994,2020]" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FD33F81FFCEBF804" box="[709,796,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Olearia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, as well as species such as 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FB43F81EFEF8F7E9" authority="Link (1822: 445)" authorityName="Link" authorityPageNumber="445" authorityYear="1822" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dealbata">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FB43F81EFA99F804" box="[1205,1390,1994,2021]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Acacia dealbata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF87FF94FA80F81FFEF8F7E9" author="Link, H. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="249" refId="ref33907" refString="Link, H. F. (1822) Enumeratio plantarum Horti regii botanici berolinensis altera 2. G. Reimer, Berolini (Berlin), Germany. 464 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / 9783112427743" type="book" year="1822">Link (1822: 445)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FEEDF83BFCF8F7E8" authority="Labill. (1806: 74)" authorityName="Labill." authorityPageNumber="74" authorityYear="1806" box="[283,783,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Atherospermataceae" genus="Atherosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moschatum">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FEEDF83BFDB7F7E8" box="[283,576,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Atherosperma moschatum</emphasis>
Labill. (1806: 74)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FCB1F83BFAB3F7E9" authority="Oerst. (1873: 355)" authorityName="Oerst." authorityPageNumber="355" authorityYear="1873" box="[839,1348,2030,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cunninghamii">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FCB1F83BFB9DF7E8" box="[839,1130,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">Nothofagus cunninghamii</emphasis>
Oerst. (1873: 355)
</taxonomicName>
. There is no information available on the elevation range of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF87FF94FD36F7C6FC98F7CC" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1868" box="[704,879,2066,2093]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF87FF94FD36F7C6FC98F7CC" box="[704,879,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="249">C. brachycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
