<paragraph id="DF656F76FF86FF95FF4BF969FB58F91A" blockId="7.[136,1452,1724,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF86FF95FF4BF969FEFEF936" bold="true" box="[189,265,1724,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="250">Notes:</emphasis>
—H.D. Schotsman took extensive notes which accompany the specimen HO 34457 suggesting that the anther of this species is trilocular. However, this requires confirmation based on fresh material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF86FF95FF4BF8D6FBD7F8A2" blockId="7.[136,1452,1724,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF86FF95FF4BF8D6FE4EF8FD" bold="true" box="[189,441,1795,1821]" pageId="7" pageNumber="250">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF86FF95FE23F8D1FD13F8FE" authorityName="Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1868" box="[469,740,1796,1822]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycarpa">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF86FF95FE23F8D1FD13F8FE" box="[469,740,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="250">Callitriche brachycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very poorly-known throughout its range, with no recent data on the conservation status of populations. It is therefore classed as Data Deficient.
</paragraph>
